  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Cook",
  "description": "<h3>Job Description</h3><ul><li><p>Prepare and cook <strong>Greek cuisine dishes</strong> according to the restaurant’s recipes and standards</p></li><li><p>Carry out daily mise en place and cooking duties under the guidance of the Head Chef / Sous Chef</p></li><li><p>Assist in operating assigned kitchen stations during service hours</p></li><li><p>Ensure consistency in food quality, taste, and presentation</p></li><li><p>Maintain kitchen cleanliness and hygiene in compliance with HACCP and NEA regulations</p></li><li><p>Handle and store food ingredients properly to minimize wastage</p></li><li><p>Assist with stock checking and basic kitchen inventory</p></li><li><p>Follow kitchen procedures, food safety, and workplace safety guidelines</p></li></ul><h3>Job Requirements</h3><ul><li><p>Minimum 2 years of relevant experience as a Cook / Line Cook</p></li><li><p>Basic experience or exposure to Greek or Mediterranean cuisine preferred</p></li><li><p>Knowledge of grilling, hot kitchen operations, and food preparation techniques</p></li><li><p>Able to work efficiently in a fast-paced kitchen environment</p></li><li><p>Familiar with food hygiene and safety standards</p></li><li><p>Willing to work shifts, weekends, and public holidays</p></li></ul><h3>Salary</h3><p><p>SGD 2,200 – 3,500 per month (commensurate with experience)<br /><br /></p><h3>Interested applicants,</h3><p>Please send your detailed CV to moo@bezcareers.com<br /><br />EA Registration No : R1440698 / Licence Number : 07C4571</p></p><h3></h3>",
